		<itunes:summary> Certainly one of the most welcomed winter holidays, in Italy the &#8220;Carnevale&#8221; (Carnival) is a huge event celebrated with parades, masquerade balls, music, entertainment, and parties. Pranks of any kind are common during &#8220;Carnevale&#8221;, so much that the saying &#8220;A Carnevale ogni scherzo vale&#8221; (During Carnival anything goes) has become part of the Italian language and culture. &#8211; A few VIP Members asked this simple question: &#8220;What is Carnival like in Italy?&#8221; &#8211; So, here&#8217;s the answer, of course, all in Italian. Enjoy!
