			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Our friend and VIP Member Anna sent us a lovely email a few days ago. She says she&#8217;s currently taking an Italian class but she&#8217;s having some trouble with the Italian expressions of time that use the verbs &#8220;Metterci&#8221; and &#8220;Volerci&#8221;, which are usually translated in English with the meaning of &#8220;It Takes&#8221;. Then she says: &#8220;Jane and Massimo, I need you to cover this soon, as my finals are around the corner!&#8221; &#8211; You asked, we listened, Anna! </p>
<p>So here it is, the nitty-gritty of the important, must-know Italian verbs &#8220;metterci&#8221; and &#8220;volerci&#8221;.  &#8212; Then as usual, after listening to the story, take the &#8220;7 Question Challenge&#8221; to test your comprehension, speaking, and grammar skills. Enjoy!</p>
