			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Alexandra, a longtime friend and VIP Member, who a couple of years ago left everything behind to fulfill her lifetime dream of living in Italy, sent us a terrific email. Recently, she felt that she needed a new hairstyle, so she clipped a photo from a magazine with the hairstyle she&#8217;d like to have, went to a beauty salon, and announced: &#8220;This is the way I want my hair to look. Let&#8217;s do it!&#8221; &#8211; Wow, talking about being decisive, Alexandra! </p>
<p>So, let&#8217;s hear Alexandra&#8217;s story (almost) as it happened and let&#8217;s learn a lot of useful &#8220;ready-to-use&#8221; Italian words and sentences that will greatly improve your knowledge of Italian. &#8211; Then as usual, after listening to the dialogue, take the &#8220;7 Question Challenge&#8221; to test your comprehension, speaking, and grammar skills.  Enjoy!</p>
