			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Longtime VIP Member Alice sent us a great email from Rome, Italy. She was in a bus a few days ago when &#8220;il controllore&#8221; (the ticket controller) jumped in and started checking tickets. &#8211; &#8220;What followed,&#8221; &#8211; she says &#8211; &#8220;can only be described as comedy at its very best. There was this woman without a ticket, and she would say anything in order not to get a fine. &#8211; I know the fact itself isn&#8217;t funny at all, but the tone of the conversation made me feel like I was in a sitcom!&#8221;</p>
<p>So, let&#8217;s pay a tribute to &#8220;real-life Italian comedy&#8221;, as Alice defines it, by listening to a conversation between a woman caught without the ticket on a bus and the ticket controller&#8221;. &#8211; Then as usual, after listening to the dialogue, take the &#8220;7 Question Challenge&#8221; to test your comprehension, speaking, and grammar skills. Enjoy!</p>
