			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Episode #26 of the fun-to-practice and extra-useful &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221; lesson series is entitled &#8220;We All Scream For Ice Cream&#8221; &#8211; Summer&#8217;s here, and with summer, comes ice cream! &#8211; &#8220;Gelato&#8221; (the Italian word for &#8220;ice cream&#8221;), is loved by kids and adults alike, it is arguably the most famous dessert in the world, and it is indeed a must on hot summer days! &#8212; Let&#8217;s celebrate the beginning of summer by finding out a few curiosities and facts about this delicious dessert. &#8211; Then as usual, after listening to the story, take the &#8220;7 Question Challenge&#8221; to test your comprehension, speaking, and grammar skills. Enjoy!</p>
