		<description><![CDATA[Learn Italian with www.LearnItalianPod.com &#8211; Episode #17 of the fun-to-practice and extra-useful &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221; lesson series is entitled &#8220;A Room For Two, Please&#8221; &#8211; Making a hotel room reservation over the phone in Italian can be a real challenge; not only on the phone you can only rely on the words spoken and [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with www.LearnItalianPod.com &#8211;  Episode #17 of the fun-to-practice and extra-useful &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221; lesson series is entitled &#8220;A Room For Two, Please&#8221; &#8211; Making a hotel room reservation over the phone in Italian can be a real challenge; not only on the phone you can only rely on the words spoken and tone of voice, but your body language is not there to assist you in communicating. </p>
<p>So, let&#8217;s go back to the basics of how to book a hotel room but with the added challenge of doing it over the phone. &#8211; By studying and practicing this episode, you will learn some useful sentences and vocabulary that you most likely will be using when booking a room or any accomodation in Italian, in person or over the phone. Enjoy!</p>
