		<title>12. This Is Your Captain Speaking (Listen Up &amp; Learn)</title>
		<link>http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2011/02/20/12-this-is-your-captain-speaking-listen-up-learn/</link>
		<comments>http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2011/02/20/12-this-is-your-captain-speaking-listen-up-learn/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 21 Feb 2011 00:41:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>LearnItalianPod.com</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen Up & Learn]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[transportation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[travel]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2011/02/20/12-this-is-your-captain-speaking-listen-up-learn/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Learn Italian with www.LearnItalianPod.com &#8211; Episode #12 of the extra-useful &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221; lesson series is entitled &#8220;This Is Your Captain Speaking&#8221; &#8211; Imagine that your are in Italy, sitting on a plane that is taxiing out to the runway for takeoff. You are about to fly to Rome where you will spend a [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with www.LearnItalianPod.com &#8211;  Episode #12 of the extra-useful &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221; lesson series is entitled &#8220;This Is Your Captain Speaking&#8221; &#8211; Imagine that your are in Italy, sitting on a plane that is taxiing out to the runway for takeoff. You are about to fly to Rome where you will spend a few days of well deserved vacation. All of a sudden, the captain is speaking through the PA system: listen to the captain&#8217;s announcement and train your ears to truly understand the Italian language! &#8212; Then, after listening to the announcement, take the &#8220;7 Question Challenge&#8221; and test your comprehension, speaking, and grammar skills by answering to seven challenging questions. Enjoy!</p>
<p><font color="#DF110F">[<strong>New Extra Bonus: Airport &#038; Planes - VIP Members Only</strong>]</font> Login to the <a href="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/lip/"><strong>Learning Center</strong></a> to find, as a special extra bonus, a super useful audio file with PDF transcript entitled &#8220;<strong>Airport &#038; Planes</strong>&#8220;, a terrific way to test and improve your knowledge of Italian by practicing listening comprehension and pronunciation. &#8211; Learn and practice all the vocabulary you need to know to make your next (Italian) flight a joy!</p>
