		<title>1. Letter To A Friend (Listen Up &amp; Learn)</title>
		<link>http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2010/11/01/1-letter-to-a-friend-listen-up-learn/</link>
		<comments>http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2010/11/01/1-letter-to-a-friend-listen-up-learn/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 Nov 2010 02:55:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>LearnItalianPod.com</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen Up & Learn]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[comprehension]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2010/11/01/1-letter-to-a-friend-listen-up-learn/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Learn Italian with the newest show on LearnItalianPod.com: &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221;, episode #1! &#8212; Of the four basic Italian language skills, reading, writing, listening and speaking, one of the most difficult to acquire is listening comprehension. &#8211; It&#8217;s a well known fact that the majority of people don&#8217;t attempt to speak a foreign language [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with the newest show on LearnItalianPod.com: &#8220;Listen Up &#038; Learn&#8221;, episode #1! &#8212; Of the four basic Italian language skills, reading, writing, listening and speaking, one of the most difficult to acquire is listening comprehension. &#8211; It&#8217;s a well known fact that the majority of people don&#8217;t attempt to speak a foreign language even when they have the chance to do it because they do not fully understand what is being said, so they become insecure and miss the chance to practice and truly learn the language. &#8212; But it doesn&#8217;t have to be that way. In fact, LearnItalianPod.com is here to the rescue with this new, exciting series that will train your ears to listen and understand the Italian language. Enjoy!</p>
