			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with LearnItalianPod.com &#8211;  Some says that the only two things you need when visiting Italy are &#8220;stomaco vuoto&#8221; (an empty stomach), and &#8220;un grande appetito&#8221; (a big appetite). It is a very well known fact that Italian meals can be long multi-course affairs, particularly when visiting, staying with a family, or celebrating any events. </p>
<p>Yes, Italians love long meals, and it&#8217;s definitely not by chance that Italian cuisine is considered &#8220;una delle migliori cucine del mondo&#8221; (one of the best cuisines in the world). &#8212; So, let&#8217;s have a lot of fun by reverse-engineering, course by course, a classic big Italian meal, all the while learning and practicing a lot of very useful Italian words, sentences, and grammar rules that are sure to make your Italian better. Enjoy!</p>
