			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with LearnItalianPod.com &#8211;   &#8220;Carosello&#8221; (in English: &#8220;Carousel&#8221; or &#8220;Merry-Go-Round&#8221;), was a very famous ten-minute advertising program broadcasted every evening from 8:50 to 9:00 PM on Italian national TV, and it ran for twenty years straight from the late Fifties until the late Seventies.  &#8220;Carosello&#8221; was a huge success and, for generations of Italian kids, the end of a Carosello episode marked the time to go to bed. </p>
<p>So, let&#8217;s learn about one of the most famous Italian cultural icons ever, &#8220;Carosello&#8221;, all while learning and practicing a lot of very useful Italian words, sentences, and grammar rules that are sure to make your Italian better. Enjoy!</p>
