			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with LearnItalianPod.com &#8211;  Learn Italian with LearnItalianPod.com &#8211;  Episode #15 of LearnItalianPod &#8220;5 Minutes A Day&#8221; lesson series is now live! This one is entitled &#8220;To Stay or To Be: That Is The Question&#8221;. Several LearnItalianPod VIP Members have requested that we explained why and when the verb &#8220;stare&#8221; (to stay) is used versus the verb &#8220;essere&#8221; (to be). Although both &#8220;essere&#8221; and &#8220;stare&#8221; mean &#8220;to be&#8221;, they are not interchangeable, and this can create a bit of confusion to students of Italian. &#8212; So, let&#8217;s shed some light on these two verbs and let&#8217;s try, once and for all, to answer the question: &#8220;To Stay or To Be?&#8221;. Enjoy!</p>
