		<title>43. Agosto, Moglie Mia Non Ti Conosco (Culture Shot)</title>
		<link>http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2009/08/16/43-agosto-moglie-mia-non-ti-conosco-culture-shot/</link>
		<comments>http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2009/08/16/43-agosto-moglie-mia-non-ti-conosco-culture-shot/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 17 Aug 2009 01:04:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>LearnItalianPod.com</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Culture Shot]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[shopping]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[traditions]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.learnitalianpod.com/2009/08/16/43-agosto-moglie-mia-non-ti-conosco-culture-shot/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Learn Italian with LearnItalianPod. LearnItalianPod VIP subscriber Alexandra from Vancouver is in Italy for study reasons. She says: &#8220;It&#8217;s the week of mid-August here in Milano and I wasn&#8217;t really prepared for what appears to be a desert city. I mean, it is&#8230; empty! Where&#8217;s everyone? And what&#8217;s with the sentence &#8220;agosto, moglie mia non [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Learn Italian with LearnItalianPod. LearnItalianPod VIP subscriber Alexandra from Vancouver is in Italy for study reasons. She says: &#8220;It&#8217;s the week of mid-August here in Milano and I wasn&#8217;t really prepared for what appears to be a desert city. I mean, it is&#8230; empty! Where&#8217;s everyone? And what&#8217;s with the sentence &#8220;agosto, moglie mia non ti conosco&#8221; that I keep hearing all the times?&#8221;</p>
<p>Dear Alexandra, welcome to the Italian &#8220;Ferragosto&#8221;, and thanks for the inspiration! &#8211; So, here they are, one of the most famous Italian summer&#8217;s sentences ever and a celebration of the Italian summer all in one Culture Shot. Enjoy!</p>
