			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.learnitalianpod.com/wp-content/imgs/bg-flag.gif" alt="LearnItalianPod" />Welcome to all of you Italian learners to the newest show on LearnItalianPod.com: &#8220;Canta Che Ti Passa&#8221;, episode #1! One of the easiest and most fun way to improve every aspect of your Italian, including pronunciation, grammar, vocabulary, and expression, and at the same time to learn more about Italian culture, is through&#8230;Italian music! </p>
<p>So here it is, the newest LearnItalianPod show that will teach you how to dramatically improve your Italian through its most famous songs! In this first episode of the show, we start with the all time Italian classic, perhaps the most well-known Italian song ever: that is &#8220;Nel Blu Dipinto di Blu&#8221;, also known as &#8220;Volare&#8221;, sung by the great Domenico Modugno. So, let&#8217;s learn pronunciation, idiomatic expressions, cultural facts, and more about this great song! Happy singing, everyone! </p>
